.TH HULAK 1 "May 2026" "hulak" "General Commands Manual"

.SH NAME
hulak \- file-based API client for the terminal

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B hulak
.br
.B hulak run [\-\-debug] [\-\-dry-run] [\-\-env] [\-\-q] [\-\-seq] [\-\-show] [\-\-ssh-identity] [\-\-timeout] <path>
.br
.B hulak version
.br
.B hulak init [\-\-env] [\-\-ssh] [\-\-ssh-identity] [envNames] <subcommand> [options]
.br
.B hulak example [\-\-o] [\-\-out] [type]
.br
.B hulak migrate <files>
.br
.B hulak doctor [\-\-fix] [\-\-json] [\-\-yes]
.br
.B hulak gql [\-\-env] <path>
.br
.B hulak secrets <subcommand> [options]
.br
.B hulak help
.br
.PP
Supported shorthand forms:
.br
.B hulak
[\-env <environment>] \-fp <file_path> [\-debug]
.br
.B hulak
[\-env <environment>] \-f <file_name> [\-debug]
.br
.B hulak
[\-env <environment>] \-dir <directory_path> [\-debug]
.br
.B hulak
[\-env <environment>] \-dirseq <directory_path> [\-debug]

.SH DESCRIPTION
Hulak runs API requests defined in YAML files. The recommended style is command\-first usage with
.B hulak run <path>
, where <path> is either a single request file or a directory of request files.
.PP
Running hulak with no file or directory target opens the interactive picker. Hulak asks you to pick
a request file first, and only asks for an environment when the selected request uses template values
like {{.token}}.
.PP
Hulak also includes a GraphQL explorer through the gql subcommand for schema discovery, operation
search, query building, execution, and saving generated files.

.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B run
Run API request file(s) or directory
.TP
.B version
Print hulak version
.TP
.B init
Initialize a hulak project
.TP
.B example
Scaffold an example request file
.TP
.B migrate
Migrate Postman collections to hulak format
.TP
.B doctor
Check project health
.TP
.B gql
Open the GraphQL explorer
.TP
.B secrets
Manage encrypted environment secrets
.TP
.B help
Show help for hulak

.SH RUN FLAGS
.TP
.B \-\-debug
Enable debug mode
.TP
.B \-\-dry-run
Print the built request and exit without sending it
.TP
.B \-\-env, \-\-environment <string>
Environment to use
.TP
.B \-\-q, \-\-quiet
Suppress the end\-of\-run summary table
.TP
.B \-\-seq, \-\-sequential
Run directory files sequentially
.TP
.B \-\-show
Reveal sensitive headers (Authorization, Cookie, etc\&.) in \-\-dry\-run output
.TP
.B \-\-ssh-identity <string>
Path to SSH private key for vault decryption
.TP
.B \-\-timeout <duration>
Per\-request timeout, e\&.g\&. 5m or 90s (default 60s)

.SH GLOBAL SHORTHAND FLAGS
These root flags remain supported, but
.B hulak run <path>
is the preferred form for examples and onboarding.

.TP
.B \-\-debug
Enable debug mode for full request/response details
.TP
.B \-\-dir <string>
Directory path to run concurrently
.TP
.B \-\-dirseq <string>
Directory path to run in alphabetical order
.TP
.B \-\-dry-run
Print the built request and exit without sending it
.TP
.B \-\-env, \-\-environment <string>
Environment file to use during the call
.TP
.B \-\-f, \-\-file <string>
File name for making an API request (case\-insensitive)
.TP
.B \-\-fp, \-\-file-path <string>
Relative (or absolute) file path of the request file
.TP
.B \-\-q, \-\-quiet
Suppress the end\-of\-run summary table
.TP
.B \-\-show
Reveal sensitive headers (Authorization, Cookie, etc\&.) in \-\-dry\-run output
.TP
.B \-\-timeout <duration>
Per\-request timeout, e\&.g\&. 5m or 90s (default 60s)

.SH INTERACTIVE MODE
.TP
.B hulak
Open the interactive request picker.
.TP
.B hulak \-env staging
Open the interactive picker with a preselected environment.
.PP
In non\-interactive shells, you should pass a file or directory target instead of relying on the picker.

.SH ENVIRONMENT SETUP
Create a project directory and initialize it with:
.PP
.RS
hulak init
.RE
.PP
To create named environment files immediately:
.PP
.RS
hulak init \-env staging prod
.RE
.PP
Hulak uses env/ files only when request files need template resolution such as {{.key}}.

.SH EXAMPLES
